name: SBC Public Health
tweet: Mantenga a los niños seguros: ¡vacunar! La vacuna COVID-19 protege a todos, incluidos los niños y los jóvenes, de contraer el virus. Para obtener más información, visite  https://t.co/PFi9B6d1mY. ¿Preguntas? Hable con su doctor.  https://t.co/t4sc6TKUjW

tweet: Keep kids safe: vaccinate! The COVID-19 vaccine protects everyone, including children and youth, from getting the virus. For more information, visit  https://t.co/5eL7V2X9Ml. Questions? Talk to your doctor.  https://t.co/CTFhzrskOU

name: SBC Public Health
tweet: Essential workers: You keep our communities running amid #COVID19. Flu vaccination can help keep you healthy so you can continue your vital work. It’s not too late to get your flu shot! Find a vaccination location near you:  https://t.co/UamlfEjwLA icon #FightFlu  https://t.co/QVTRITxqrG

name: SBC Public Health
tweet: The Health Officer Order for indoor mask use, regardless of vaccination status, has been extended in #SantaBarbaraCounty. Remember to wear your mask when in indoor spaces outside your home. More information here:  https://t.co/WofrOC5qCQ  https://t.co/uyaBsfmxUI

name: SBC Public Health
tweet: DYK? It’s National Influenza Vaccination Week, a reminder that there’s still time to get vaccinated. When more people are protected against flu, it is less likely to spread. To learn more about benefits of flu vaccination visit:  https://t.co/0xWJQv6zib  https://t.co/mFI9OnpePx
